verses.verse: Kain, Gibeah, and Timnah: ten cities with their villages;
Maarath, Beth Anoth, and Eltekon: six cities with their villages;
(Josh. 18:14; 1 Sam. 7:1, 2) Kirjath Baal (which is Kirjath Jearim) and Rabbah: two cities with their villages.
In the wilderness: Beth Arabah, Middin, Secacah,
Nibshan, the City of Salt, and (1 Sam. 23:29; Ezek. 47:10) En Gedi: six cities with their villages.

As for the Jebusites, the inhabitants of Jerusalem, (Judg. 1:8, 21; 2 Sam. 5:6; 1 Chr. 11:4) the children of Judah could not drive them out; (Judg. 1:21) but the Jebusites dwell with the children of Judah at Jerusalem to this day.

Ephraim and West Manasseh The lot fell to the children of Joseph from the Jordan, by Jericho, to the waters of Jericho on the east, to the (Josh. 8:15; 18:12) wilderness that goes up from Jericho through the mountains to Bethel,
